<br>
Sitting in BB waiting on Walnan to spawn, some newb (lvl 12) monkie proceeded to spam inspect me.  I stood up /d'ed him then sat back down.  He ran to the local guards (that are visible from Walnan's spawn point), then accepted my /d.<br>
<br>
I went ahead and Bolted him, and was easily able to run out of follow range from the guards before they could do much more than turn around (waited for dmg message then booked for a couple seconds).<br>
<br>
The monk was dead and I was able to return to my wait for Walnan since it was out of guards chase range anyway (not sure if they were agro'ed, though I am sure they were).  <br>
<br>
Monkie tells you, haha newb have fun with the guards<br>
<br>
You tell monkie, what guards?<br>
<br>
Monkie comes back (he was bound close, he was back within a minute). Spam inspects me again, so I proceed with the /d again. <br>
<br>
Naturally, I had a guess at where he was going with this so I /invited him to the group.<br>
<br>
This time he &quot;thinks&quot; he is smarter, and runs to the gfay/lfay zoneline before accepting.<br>
<br>
Monkie tells you, bring it<br>
<br>
You tell monkie, would if I could find you<br>
<br>
Monkie tells you, LMAO newb<br>
<br>
You tell Monkie, ohh wait, I think I know where you are...<br>
<br>
Monkie tells you, where?<br>
<br>
You tell monkie, right beside me<br>
<br>
/cast 6<br>
<br>
Monkie tells you, LMAO newb<br>
<br>
/pet attack<br>
<br>
Monkie tells you, I think I'll zone now newb<br>
<br>
You tell monkie, Too Late NEWB<br>
<br>
You have slain Monkie<br>
<br>
Monkie tells you, WTF<br>
<br>
Then Walnan Spawned and  I CoH'ed my buds mage over so he could do his turn in (he was xp'ing guards by the docks while we waited).<br>
<br>
Ohh yes and I was unanon and not in RP at the time.  Me and my bud sat there laughing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kathodos>Kathodos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 328<br> <font color=#333333>(1/3/03 5:42:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergoofystuff.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.battle.net/war3/images/human/units/portraits/waterelement.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: N00B memories..</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baervon:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> It seems he would give newbs 20pp to drown themselves in the lake. He said it made him laugh. I told him he was one sick dude. He's still one of my best friends in game LOL.<br>
<br>
And THAT is the funniest thing I remember seeing in EQ for a long, long time. Newbies choking to death. For 20pp. *chuckle*<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Back around the Kunark era, before Nexus and PoK, one of the best melee bind points before raids (PoH especially) was Greater Fay because you could bind the melees and casters all at the spires for easy collection by a Wizard.<br>
<br>
A few members of my guild would pay newbies 10 - 50pp for newbies to jump from the top of the spires. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><br>
<br>
I also remember just before PoP I was sitting in The Arena with a druid friend training rare languages (as you have to zone after each point, a druid succor in Arena was the quickest way to zone).<br>
<br>
A guild of about 25 players, levels between 35 - 50, begins to zone in and bind using the soulbinder, as they had planned to have a guild event in the Arena.<br>
<br>
As I was level 60, I was walking around in the Arena watching their duels assuming none of them would try to engage me.  A level 36'ish druid decided he'd take a go at me, so I invis'd, walked off to a corner, and summoned my epic pet, fully buffed it, then walked back into the centre of the Arena and set the pet to guard.<br>
<br>
The druid ran up, looked at me, turned to look at the pet, cast SoW on himself, nuked me then made a break for the Arena PvE/PvP border and safety.  He didn't make it 5 feet before Jobantik ripped him apart (/thank Velocity).  The rest of his guild slowly started attacking the pet one at a time, and getting killed off.   Then they tried attacking in small groups.<br>
<br>
Eventually their guild leader (50 warrior with a 60 monk alt, who I'd been chatting with while this was happening) formed them up, and they used the epic pet as a raid mob. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   They had set up cleric complete heal chains, the works.  Was going well for them, until one of their clerics gained CH healing aggro, and the pet switched to the Cleric!  I didn't order the pet too, so it took me by surprise.  Their healing promptly fell apart, and the pet started cleaning them up.  A few of the less valiant members made a break for the Arena entrance, but the pet caught up with them and dropped them about 2 feet from safety.<br>
<br>
I was laughing so hard it hurt. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Their guild leader came back with his 60 monk to tank (using a 2H'er) and I used the pet commands to keep aggro on him and made sure the pet didn't switch targets.  Their 25 or so people completed their &quot;raid&quot; on this second attempt, only losing a few.  Was a lot of fun for them and me, and after several of them had thanked me for the fun, and I them, I left. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59365" target="top">Kathodos</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Battle Cleric of Tunare - Tholuxe Paells<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=279732" target="top">Kantreach</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Arch Mage Antagonist - Tholuxe Paells</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergoofystuff>Goofy Stuff</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
